ğŸ Road Safety Snakes & Ladders

An educational Snakes & Ladders game built in Python using Kivy, designed to promote road safety awareness through gameplay.

This project was originally developed during Class 11 as part of a school assignment, using a fixed, non-uniform road safety board image, which required manual pixel-based coordinate mapping for player movement.

ğŸ¯ Purpose

The goal of this game is to make learning traffic rules and road safety concepts engaging by integrating them into a familiar board game format.

Snakes represent traffic violations

Ladders represent good road safety practices

Each event displays an educational message

ğŸ•¹ï¸ Features

Two-player gameplay

Dice roll with sound effects

Snakes & ladders with contextual messages

Keyboard controls (Space to roll dice, Esc to exit)

Animated player movement

Menu screen with About section

Compiled Windows executable (EXE)

ğŸ§  Technical Highlights

Built using Python + Kivy

Manual mapping of player positions to a non-uniform board image

Pixel-based coordinate calculations adapted to screen scaling

Sound effects and animations for improved user experience

Asset handling compatible with packaged executables

ğŸ–¥ï¸ Requirements

Windows OS (7 or later)

No Python installation required if using the EXE
(Python 3.x + Kivy required only for running from source)

